"{\"uid\": \"standard.co.uk-sport-sport-olympics-andy-murray-paris-olympics-2024-tennis-dan-evans-doubles-b1174319.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"To use the search feature, we need your consent to load Google Custom Search, which may use cookies or similar technologies.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 124, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 56, \"end\": 76, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Google Custom Search\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Google_Programmable_Search_Engine\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Please click 'Allow and Continue' below to enable search.\", \"from\": 125, \"to\": 182, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"See our privacy policy for more information.\", \"from\": 183, \"to\": 227, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sport|Olympics  Not this time - and now, not ever again.\", \"from\": 229, \"to\": 285, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On Thursday night here in Paris, the grand farewell finally ran out of great escapes,Andy Murrayout of theOlympicsand the professional game.\", \"from\": 287, \"to\": 427, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 313, \"end\": 318, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9921310187406618e-18, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He and partnerDan Evanshave given so much to the first week of these Games, their journey to this quarter-final an epic tale of resilience and late-night comebacks, of seven match-points saved, including five on the spin when it seemed it might be over before it had begun.\", \"from\": 429, \"to\": 702, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Naturally, we had all begun to wonder whether, in breach of all logic, this might actually be on, the British pair suddenly within one win of a guaranteed shot at a parting medal and seemingly with some higher force on side.\", \"from\": 704, \"to\": 928, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 806, \"end\": 813, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999551171922556, \"rank\": 3.183282668728785e-05, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead, the fairytale was torn up by the high-class Americans, Taylor Fritz and Tommy Paul, who with a 6-2 6-4 win move into the last-four.\", \"from\": 930, \"to\": 1070, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 994, \"end\": 1006, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taylor_Fritz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Taylor Fritz\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taylor_Fritz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taylor_Fritz\"}, {\"begin\": 1011, \"end\": 1021, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tommy_Paul\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.332576987784649e-19, \"text\": \"Tommy Paul\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tommy_Paul\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tommy_Paul\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"And with that, the thing that's been coming, for years, really, but with absolute certainty for the last month, had arrived: the end of the road for one of Britain's greatest ever sportsmen, the winner of three Grand Slams, two Olympic gold medals and one long, torturous battle against body and time.\", \"from\": 1072, \"to\": 1373, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1228, \"end\": 1235, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"score\": 0.9999981721733426, \"rank\": 1.8069421474983778e-06, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_Kingdom\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Every morning since being knocked out of Wimbledon a month ago, Murray has woken with a dodgy back and the unsettling burden that his next tennis match might be his last.\", \"from\": 1375, \"to\": 1545, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1439, \"end\": 1445, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0301052961824906e-33, \"text\": \"Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This week, he has three times made the journey to Roland-Garros knowing he might not return.\", \"from\": 1546, \"to\": 1638, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For those of us with a watching brief, these repeat pilgrimages to Paris's west have come to feel a little like dark tourism, each visit in anticipation of a glorious career's dying act.\", \"from\": 1640, \"to\": 1826, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1707, \"end\": 1712, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9921310187406618e-18, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Again, Murray and Evans were scheduled last on Suzanne-Lenglen, appointment viewing in what has become an appointment slot.\", \"from\": 1827, \"to\": 1950, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1834, \"end\": 1840, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0301052961824906e-33, \"text\": \"Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\"}, {\"begin\": 1845, \"end\": 1850, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Godfrey_Evans\", \"score\": 0.9999999957994987, \"rank\": 4.20039484493185e-09, \"text\": \"Evans\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Godfrey_Evans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Godfrey_Evans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For much of the evening, the roof had been closed, following a brief downpour on another otherwise scorching, stuffy day.\", \"from\": 1951, \"to\": 2072, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It made a sweatbox of the indoor arena, the stands as Felix Auger-Aliassime edged Casper Ruud in the last-eight of the singles a sea of fluttering fold-out fans and the queues for the ice cream stalls long.\", \"from\": 2074, \"to\": 2280, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2128, \"end\": 2149, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/F\\u00e9lix_Auger-Aliassime\", \"score\": 0.9999999516558103, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Felix Auger-Aliassime\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/F\\u00e9lix_Auger-Aliassime\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/F\\u00e9lix_Auger-Aliassime\"}, {\"begin\": 2156, \"end\": 2167, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Casper_Ruud\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Casper Ruud\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Casper_Ruud\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Casper_Ruud\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Blessedly, in the moments before the doubles were introduced, the roof was rolled back and the breeze let in.\", \"from\": 2281, \"to\": 2390, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Andy Murray's My London: 'A good first date?\", \"from\": 2392, \"to\": 2436, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2392, \"end\": 2403, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.780912584184899e-64, \"text\": \"Andy Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\"}, {\"begin\": 2409, \"end\": 2415, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999999997121449, \"rank\": 2.865059087319858e-10, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"McDonald's in Wandsworth'  Aquatics GB 'immensely disappointed' as Proud joins Enhanced Games  Sports quiz of 2024: 100 hard questions on an incredible year  Winter escapes and activities to end the year in style  Still, you did not envy Paul, who had already played in the hottest part of the afternoon against Carlos Alcaraz, pushing the Wimbledon champion hard but going down in straight sets.\", \"from\": 2437, \"to\": 2833, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2451, \"end\": 2461, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wandsworth\", \"score\": 0.956096468753887, \"rank\": 0.04591946440702285, \"text\": \"Wandsworth\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wandsworth\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Wandsworth\"}, {\"begin\": 2749, \"end\": 2763, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Alcaraz\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Carlos Alcaraz\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Alcaraz\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Carlos_Alcaraz\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Fritz, meanwhile, had come through a marathon assignment on Wednesday, playing three matches across singles, mixed and men's doubles in the space of nine hours.\", \"from\": 2834, \"to\": 2994, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The Brits, then, had a freshness edge.\", \"from\": 2996, \"to\": 3034, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2996, \"end\": 3005, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brit_Awards\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"The Brits\", \"types\": [\"Q618779\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brit_Awards\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Brit_Awards\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Neither American, mind you, has a metal hip.\", \"from\": 3035, \"to\": 3079, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3043, \"end\": 3051, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9996544874342214, \"rank\": 0.0003239477647937425, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They started best, up a double-break in no time with Paul lethal at the net and up the line, and the first set as good as gone.\", \"from\": 3080, \"to\": 3207, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Again, there were as more seats empty than employed, but half-a-home crowd is better than a full house without skin in the game.\", \"from\": 3209, \"to\": 3337, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Here, whether Brits, romantics or both, almost all were cheering one way whenever they had chance.\", \"from\": 3338, \"to\": 3436, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Which, for a long time, was not all that often, the Brits unable to make any momentum stick.\", \"from\": 3438, \"to\": 3530, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Evans took his frustration out on some flowers and earned pantomime boos from the horticulturally aware.\", \"from\": 3531, \"to\": 3635, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"When the chair umpire had to ask for quiet, it was only to stop a lone American from murdering 'The Star-Spangled Banner'.\", \"from\": 3636, \"to\": 3758, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3707, \"end\": 3715, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9996544874342214, \"rank\": 0.0003239477647937425, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Evans serve was broken, the Americans 4-1 up in the second and Britain on the brink.\", \"from\": 3760, \"to\": 3848, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3764, \"end\": 3769, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Godfrey_Evans\", \"score\": 0.9999999957994987, \"rank\": 4.20039484493185e-09, \"text\": \"Evans\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Godfrey_Evans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Godfrey_Evans\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They had come from a set and a break down against the Japanese in their opening encounter, but this was an even greater ask.\", \"from\": 3849, \"to\": 3973, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3903, \"end\": 3911, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\", \"score\": 0.9606036532315424, \"rank\": 0.0378079800956489, \"text\": \"Japanese\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Japanese_language\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Perhaps predictably, they broke back immediately, a here-we-go-again sliver of false hope?\", \"from\": 3975, \"to\": 4065, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Murray double-faulted - 5-2 to the US - and for the first time looked resigned, a well-earned, if not particularly wanted retirement now only a few hits away.\", \"from\": 4066, \"to\": 4224, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4066, \"end\": 4072, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.0301052961824906e-33, \"text\": \"Murray\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10833314\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Andy_Murray\"}, {\"begin\": 4101, \"end\": 4103, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9994467051003418, \"rank\": 0.00033442300846236463, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But still he found more, a forehead smash and yet another match point saved, another act of defiance from the art's master.\", \"from\": 4226, \"to\": 4349, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Some of the rallies that followed were comically long, games edging back and forth from deuce with advantages either way, as if something in the very fabric of tennis itself did not quite want this to end.\", \"from\": 4350, \"to\": 4555, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But at 9:38pm local, to a standing ovation and chants of \\\"Andy!\", \"from\": 4557, \"to\": 4620, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Andy!\", \"from\": 4621, \"to\": 4626, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Andy!\", \"from\": 4627, \"to\": 4632, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\", at last it did.\", \"from\": 4632, \"to\": 4650, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"MORE ABOUT  Have your say...  1  Crime  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line train after youths told to stop vaping by middle-aged passenger  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line after youths told to stop vaping  2  Football  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup, confirmed team news, injury latest for Premier League today  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup and confirmed team news  3  UK  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning over Donald Trump's Iran war  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning on Iran war  4  Lifestyle  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday, March 21, 2026  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday, March 21, 2026  5  Football  Arsenal XI vs Man City: Confirmed team news, predicted lineup, injury latest for Carabao Cup final  Arsenal XI vs Man City: Confirmed team news and predicted lineup\", \"from\": 4652, \"to\": 5530, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4712, \"end\": 4721, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Elizabeth_II\", \"score\": 0.999993143624437, \"rank\": 4.598915434217138e-06, \"text\": \"El